# Visual Bible Feature — Walkthrough

## Summary
Implemented automatic Visual Bible generation for historical video processing. When the **Historical** constraint is checked, the app generates a structured reference document before processing individual segments.

## Changes Made

### New Files
| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| [narrative_review.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/narrative_review.py) | Generate, save, and load Visual Bible documents |
| [narrative_review_prompt.txt](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/prompts/narrative_review_prompt.txt) | Prompt template for AI analysis |

### Modified Files
| File | Changes |
|---|---|
| [prompt_generator.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/prompt_generator.py) | Added [visual_bible](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/narrative_review.py#31-46) parameter to all generation methods; prepends bible as reference section in user messages |
| [process_controller.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/core/process_controller.py) | Integrated Visual Bible step — loads cached or generates new (Pro tier), saves to file, passes to prompt generator |

## Processing Flow
```
Historical ✓ → Start Processing
  ├─ Cached _visual_bible.txt? → Load it
  └─ No cache? → AI (Pro) reads full SRT → generates bible → saves file
  → Each segment gets Visual Bible prepended as reference
  → AI uses relevant characters/settings per segment
```

